Queen regent Noloyiso Sandile of Rharhabe DURBAN - AmaRharhabe Kingdom Queen Regent Noloyiso Sandile has died from COVID-19-related complications. READ: Western Cape Premier tests positive for COVID-19 The 56-year-old Queen was wife to the late AmaRharhabe King Maxhoba Sandile. She was also the sister of AmaZulu monarch king Goodwill Zwelithini. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.